This paper deals with the design of a secure auction protocol, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also involves game theory concepts, which could place it under the category of theoretical computer science (cs.GT). The proposed technique involves the use of a knapsack problem, which is a well-known optimization problem in computer science, placing it under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, which could place it under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
